{
  "title": "The Victorian Mother's Anger Over Computers",
  "content": "In the quaint Victorian era, Mrs. Smith sat at her desk, a steaming cup of tea in hand. Her eyes scanned through the pages of her book, but her mind was elsewhere. She had always been an advocate for technology, believing it would revolutionize society. But now, as she watched her children play video games and surf the internet, she couldn't help but feel a pang of anger. The world had changed too quickly, and she feared that her children were losing touch with the world around them. She longed to return to simpler times when books were the only source of knowledge. But now, as she sat at her desk, staring at the screen of her computer, she knew it was too late. Her Victorian motherly instincts had been replaced by a fierce anger towards technology."
  , "word_count": 102
  , "style_elements": ["historical", "anger"]
}

