    "content": "In a time where technology dominated, there was one woman determined to preserve her heritage. She had lived through the Industrial Revolution and knew what it meant to survive. Yet, with the advent of electricity and the first computers, she found herself envious. The Victorian mother sat on her rocking chair and gazed at the glowing screens. Each keystroke brought her back in time - not the good old days but those filled with hardship. She loved the simplicity of writing letters by hand; it was a connection to the past that computers could never replicate."
